      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; selection of SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen hemolysis power-law is documented and justified.",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty assessment is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-omega turbulence closure and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model were selected based on published literature precedent for blood pump CFD."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs including blood viscosity, inlet velocity profiles, and rotational speed must be characterized with documented uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Uncertainty quantification was performed on the four primary model inputs: blood dynamic viscosity (±8%), inlet flow rate (±3%), rotational speed (±1%), and hematocrit (±5%). Monte Carlo propagation across 500 samples yields a 95th-percentile NIH bound of 0.018 mg/100L, remaining below the acceptance threshold. Note: ranking of dominant input contributors via formal sensitivity analysis is planned for a future revision of this assessment."
    },
